Ahhh, I know why. It's because API_KEY and SERVER_API_KEY have the same id value as per the OS implementation:
IdentityProvider const IdentityProviderUserAPIKey = "api-key";
IdentityProvider const IdentityProviderServerAPIKey = "api-key";

🤷
I remember I mentioned it and we agreed it was a bit silly, but we needed to keep it separate because of the OS implementation, although being technically the same thing, treats them as two different identity providers. That's why the test passes.

